Guided Exercise: Protect Internal Traffic with TLS
Goal of This Exercise (Concept)
In Kubernetes/OpenShift, applications inside the cluster communicate through Services.
By default this traffic can be unencrypted (HTTP).
For security, we want:
•	Encrypted communication (HTTPS)
•	TLS certificates automatically managed by OpenShift
•	Pods trust the OpenShift certificate authority
This exercise shows how to:
1.	Generate TLS certificates automatically
2.	Mount certificates into the server pod
3.	Inject CA bundle into client pod
4.	Enable secure HTTPS communication inside cluster
________________________________________
2. Architecture of This Exercise
Two applications exist:
Client Pod  --->  Server Service  --->  Server Pod (NGINX)
       HTTPS request
Components used:
Component	Purpose
server deployment	NGINX HTTPS server
server service	exposes server pod
service-ca controller	generates TLS certificates
secret	stores TLS certificate
configmap	stores CA certificate
client pod	connects securely
