6. Step 3 — Generate TLS Certificate Automatically
OpenShift has a Service CA Controller.
It can automatically create certificates for services.
We enable it using annotation.
________________________________________
Command
oc annotate service server \
service.beta.openshift.io/serving-cert-secret-name=server-secret
Explanation
Part	Meaning
oc annotate	add annotation to resource
service server	modify server service
annotation	request TLS certificate
Annotation:
service.beta.openshift.io/serving-cert-secret-name=server-secret
This tells OpenShift:
Generate TLS certificate for this service and store it in secret server-secret.
________________________________________
7. What OpenShift Automatically Does
The service-ca controller:
1.	Creates TLS key
2.	Signs certificate with cluster CA
3.	Creates secret
server-secret
Secret contains:
tls.crt  -> certificate
tls.key  -> private key
________________________________________
8. Verify the Service
