10. Step 4 — Mount Secret Into Server Pod
The NGINX server expects certificates at:
/etc/pki/nginx/
So we mount the secret as a volume.
________________________________________
Patch File
spec:
  template:
    spec:
      containers:
        - name: server
          volumeMounts:
            - name: server-secret
              mountPath: /etc/pki/nginx/
      volumes:
        - name: server-secret
          secret:
            secretName: server-secret
________________________________________
Explanation
volumeMounts
Mounts volume inside container.
mountPath: /etc/pki/nginx/
Meaning certificates appear in that directory.
________________________________________
volumes
Defines volume source.
secret:
  secretName: server-secret
Meaning:
Use secret as filesystem volume.
________________________________________
Mapping Files
tls.crt -> server.crt
tls.key -> private/server.key
Used by NGINX for HTTPS.
